India 's first unmanned spacecraft will carry DthreeEuropean payload on its journey to the moon , schedule for 2007 , to be use in experiment on the lunar surface , the head of the country 's space programme say Monday .
India say it now have the capability to put heavy satellite into orbit as far as 36,000 kilometer ( 22,500 mile ) from Earth .
The Indian Space Research Organisation sign a memorandum of understand with the European Space Agency Monday to carry the additional payload aboard India 's Chandrayan-1 spacecraft , ISRO chairman G. Madhavan Nair tell reporter 
